      <h2 class="uc-section-title">Grid</h2>
      <p>You can create a grid layout by specifying the <code>uc-grid</code> class.</p>

      <div class="doc-component-box" id="c-1">
        <h3>1. Basic</h3>
        <p>Create a grid layout. </p>
        <p>Set <code>uc-grid</code> as the parent element and <code>uc-grid-child</code> as the child element. <br>You can also apply margins by adding the <code>_gutter</code> class.</p>

        <div class="doc-component-preview">
          <div class="uc-content">
            <div class="uc-grid _gutter">
              <div class="uc-grid-cell">
                <div style="padding:3em;background:white">box1</div>
              </div>
              <div class="uc-grid-cell">
                <div style="padding:3em;background:white">box2</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="uc-code-unit">
<pre><code class="html">&lt;div class="uc-grid _gutter"&gt;
  &lt;div class="uc-grid-cell"&gt;
    &lt;div style="padding:3em;background:white"&gt;box1&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class="uc-grid-cell"&gt;
    &lt;div style="padding:3em;background:white"&gt;box2&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="doc-component-box" id="c-2">
        <h3>2. Adjust column width</h3>
        <p>You can fit the width by specifying <code>_col-fit</code>, and you can place it in the full width by specifying <code>_col-full</code>.</p>

        <div class="doc-component-preview">
          <div class="uc-grid _col-fit _gutter">
            <div class="uc-grid-cell">
              <div style="padding:3em;background:white">box1</div>
            </div>
            <div class="uc-grid-cell">
              <div style="padding:3em;background:white">box2</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div>&nbsp;</div>
          <div class="uc-grid _col-full _gutter">
            <div class="uc-grid-cell">
              <div style="padding:3em;background:white">box1</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="uc-code-unit">
<pre><code class="html">&lt;!-- Adjust the width according to the number of elements. --&gt;
&lt;div class="uc-grid _col-fit _gutter"&gt;
  &lt;div class="uc-grid-cell"&gt;
    &lt;div style="padding:3em;background:white"&gt;box1&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class="uc-grid-cell"&gt;
    &lt;div style="padding:3em;background:white"&gt;box2&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;!-- Place it across the full width. --&gt;
&lt;div class="uc-grid _col-full _gutter"&gt;
  &lt;div class="uc-grid-cell"&gt;
    &lt;div style="padding:3em;background:white"&gt;box1&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="doc-component-box" id="c-3">
        <h3>3. Specify the number of columns</h3>
        <p>To modify the number of columns, specify the <code>_col-{2...12}</code> class. <br>For example, in the next sample you can place it in four columns.</p>

        <div class="doc-component-preview">
          <div class="uc-grid _col-4 _gutter">
            <div class="uc-grid-cell">
