            </div>
            <div class="uc-grid-cell _col-fit">
              <div style="padding:3em;background:white">box5</div>
            </div>
            <div class="uc-grid-cell _col-fit">
              <div style="padding:3em;background:white">box6</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="uc-code-unit">
<pre><code class="html">&lt;div class="uc-grid _col-4 _gutter"&gt;
  &lt;div class="uc-grid-cell"&gt;
    &lt;div style="padding:3em;background:white"&gt;box1&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class="uc-grid-cell"&gt;
    &lt;div style="padding:3em;background:white"&gt;box2&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class="uc-grid-cell"&gt;
    &lt;div style="padding:3em;background:white"&gt;box3&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class="uc-grid-cell"&gt;
    &lt;div style="padding:3em;background:white"&gt;box4&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;!-- It can also be specified as `uc-grid-cell`. --&gt;
  &lt;div class="uc-grid-cell _col-fit"&gt;
    &lt;div style="padding:3em;background:white"&gt;box5&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class="uc-grid-cell _col-fit"&gt;
    &lt;div style="padding:3em;background:white"&gt;box6&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="doc-component-box" id="c-4">
        <h3>4. Responsive</h3>
        <p>Specifying class <code>_small-col-{full | fit | 2...12}</code> or <code>_medium-col-{full | fit | 2...12}</code>, <br>you can change the number of columns according to screen size.</p>
        <p><code>_small-col</code> is applied when the screen width is 768px or less, and <code>_medium-col</code> is applied in the case of 769px to 1199px.</p>
        <p>In the next sample, it is changed to 3 columns when the width is 1200px or more, <br>2 columns when 1199px to 769px, and 1 column (full) when the width is 768px or less.</p>

